 KLA is a global leader in diversified electronics for the semiconductor manufacturing ecosystem. Virtually every electronic device in the world is produced using our technologies. No laptop, smartphone, wearable device, voice-controlled gadget, flexible screen, VR device or smart car would have made it into your hands without us. KLA invents systems and solutions for the manufacturing of wafers and reticles, integrated circuits, packaging, printed circuit boards and flat panel displays. The innovative ideas and devices that are advancing humanity all begin with inspiration, research and development. KLA focuses more than average on innovation and in 2019 we invested 15% of sales back into R&D. Our expert teams of physicists, engineers, data scientists and problem-solvers work together with the worldâ€™s leading technology providers to accelerate the delivery of tomorrowâ€™s electronic devices. Life here is exciting and our teams thrive on tackling really hard problems. There is never a dull moment with us.
 We are looking for an internship candidate who is passionate on Machine Learning, Deep Learning and Artificial Intelligence for applied research and product innovations in image processing and computer vision areas. A qualified candidate is expected to have strong background on image processing algorithms and deep understanding/experience on Machine Learning/Deep Learning theories. The possible tasks that the candidate will be working on includes, but not limited to,
 Understand and derive algorithms based on latest literatures and conference papers;
 Implement the state-of-the-art ML/DL algorithms in Tensorflow or PyTorch;
 Design and improve models for specific applications;
 Design new Deep Learning modules, algorithms or processes;
 Optimize and tune a ML or DL model for optimal performance;
 Evaluate and validate the model performance with respect to metrics;
 Perform A/B test between models;
 Tackle physical/science problems via ML or DL methodology;
 Communicate ideas and findings in professional presentations;
 Qualification Desired
 PhD candidate enrolled in a full-time University or Institution, in the field of Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Science or a related quantitative field.
 2 years research or industrial experience on applying Machine Learning or Deep Learning on real problems, especially for imaging processing or signal processing.
 Demonstrations on designing, exploring and validating complex learning models.
 Problem solving skills on identifying solutions.
 Proficiency in at least one programming languages including Python, Java, C/C++.
 Proficiency in Tensorflow or PyTorch.
 Technical publications, patents or open-source projects in ML, DL for imaging processing is a plus.
 Minimum Qualifications
 PhD candidate enrolled in a full-time University or Institution, in the field of Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Science or a related quantitative field.
 Some experience on applying Machine Learning or Deep Learning on real problems, especially for imaging processing or signal processing.
 Proficiency in at least one programming languages including Python, Java, C/C++.
 Proficiency in Tensorflow or PyTorch.
